07 April - Broccoli-Scallion Cornbread

- 1     cup yellow cornmeal
- 2 1/2 cup all purpose flour
- 2     teaspoon baking powder
- 1     teaspoon salt
- 1     teaspon black pepper
- 2     tablespoons sugar
- 1     egg lightly beaten 
- 1     cup sour cream
- 1/2   cup yogurt or buttermilk
- 1     cup creamed corn (1 small can)
- 1/4   cup vegetable oil
- 1     cup finely chopped broccoli florets
- 2     scallions, finely chopped

Preheat oven to 350F. Butter or grease an 8-in square baking pan. Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt, black pepper and sugar in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, combine the egg, sour cream, yogurt, creamed corn, and vegetable oil. Add egg mixture to flour mixture and stir until just blended. Stir in broccoli and scallions. Spoon the batter into greased pan and bake for 45-55 minutes or until browned on top and firm to hte touch. Makes nine generous squares. 